{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17612467","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17612467"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:23:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:23:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16276"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16276","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16276"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.41,0.36,0.23,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8967"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74797"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8967","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8967"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16276"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60283"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4070"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7567"},{"type":"tags","id":"10143"},{"type":"tags","id":"10676"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21339"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21342"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74797","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74797"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 15-year-old presents for evaluation of delayed puberty. Laboratory testing reveals low testosterone and low follicle stimulating hormone (FSH) and luteinising hormone (LH) levels.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis pattern suggests hypogonadotropic hypogonadism, where the primary defect is in the hypothalamus or pituitary rather than the gonads.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a cause of hypogonadotropic hypogonadism?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Cranial irradiation","Klinefelter syndrome","Turner syndrome","Testicular trauma","Viral orchitis"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECranial irradiation\u003C/strong\u003E can damage the hypothalamus and pituitary gland, leading to decreased production of gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) and gonadotropins (FSH/LH), resulting in hypogonadotropic hypogonadism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options represent causes of primary (hypergonadotropic) hypogonadism:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKlinefelter syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E (47,XXY) causes primary testicular failure\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETurner syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E (45,X) causes primary ovarian failure\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETesticular trauma\u003C/strong\u003E directly damages the gonads\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EViral orchitis\u003C/strong\u003E causes inflammation and damage to the testes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn primary hypogonadism, gonadotropin levels are elevated due to lack of negative feedback from sex hormones. In hypogonadotropic hypogonadism, both gonadotropins and sex hormones are low due to hypothalamic-pituitary dysfunction.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Hypogonadotropic hypogonadism is characterised by low sex hormones due to decreased gonadotropin (FSH/LH) production from the pituitary.","Common causes include Kallmann syndrome, isolated GnRH deficiency, and cranial irradiation affecting the hypothalamus/pituitary.","Primary hypogonadism shows high gonadotropins while secondary (hypogonadotropic) hypogonadism shows low gonadotropins."],"references":["Fraietta R, Zylberstejn DS, Esteves SC. Hypogonadotropic hypogonadism revisited. Clinics (Sao Paulo). 2013;68 Suppl 1(Suppl 1):81-8. doi: 10.6061/clinics/2013(sup01)09. PMID: 23503957; PMCID: PMC3583156.","Millar AC, Faghfoury H, Bieniek JM. Genetics of hypogonadotropic hypogonadism. Transl Androl Urol. 2021 Mar;10(3):1401-1409. doi: 10.21037/tau.2020.03.33. PMID: 33850776; PMCID: PMC8039576.","Isaksson S, Bogefors K, \u00c5kesson K, \u00d8ra I, Egund L, Bobjer J, Leijonhufvud I, Giwercman A. Low bone mineral density is associated with hypogonadism and cranial irradiation in male childhood cancer survivors. Osteoporos Int. 2020 Jul;31(7):1261-1272. doi: 10.1007/s00198-020-05285-4. Epub 2020 Feb 1. PMID: 32008156; PMCID: PMC7280350."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60283"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16276"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60283","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60283"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-27T07:02:49+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-27T07:03:28+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8967"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74797"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":